The chairman of the Life InsurersAssociation told a press conference that life insurancecompanies  will increasingly diversify their investments awayfrom U.S. Bonds to protect themselves against currency swings,an association spokesman said.    Terumichi Tsuchida said Japanese investment in U.S. Bondsis decreasing, but not drastically,    Life insurers are increasingly placing some of their fundsin other currencies, including bonds in Canadian dlrs and inEuropean currencies, he told the conference. REUTER&#3;